<TITLE> Gazipur RMG factory fire injures 8 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, May 11 (bdnews24.com)  At least eight persons were injured when a fire broke out in a warehouse of a garment factory in Gazipur on Tuesday. The authority of Partex Denim Limited of Bangla Bazar area of Gazipur Sadr upazila said that the fire started from the godown at around 11am. Abu Zafar Ahmed, station officer of Gazipur Fire Service, said that they were able to douse fire after trying for two hours. Assistant general manager of the factory Abdul Hamid told journalists that the damages worth between Tk 18 and Tk 20 crore as the fire spread rapidly and the yarn and cloth kept in the godown burnt into ashes. The eight, including three workers Bijoy, 30, Jahir, 28, Kamal, 25, and driver Mintu, 35, were injured when they tried to douse the fire. The fire officer suspected that the fire had broken out from an electric short circuit. He said that the damage might be worth about Tk 1 crore. bdnews
